# Godog

Cucumber for golang. Cucumber is a software tool that supports behavior-driven development. Cucumber framework uses Gherkin ( A simple plain text language parser) to describe expected software behaviors logically, resulting in better communication and collaboration among technical and non-technical team members.

Visit the following resources to learn more:

- [Official Go Tutorial: Godog](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/cucumber/godog)
- [Official Github: Godog](https://github.com/cucumber/godog/tree/v0.13.0#godogs)
- [Cucumber BDD](https://cucumber.io/)